Interface MapDAO

  • All Known Implementing Classes:

    • Method Detail

      • getMaps

        java.util.List<Map> getMaps()
        Returns the list of all maps. If there is no maps, it will return a null object.
        Returns:
        the maps on the database

      • getMap

        Map getMap​(int mid)
        Returns a map selected by its id. If there is not map matching, it will return a null object.
        Parameters:
        mid - the map identifier
        Returns:
        the map

      • createMap

        boolean createMap​(int uid,
                  java.lang.String creator,
                  boolean access)
        Creates a map.
        Parameters:
        uid - the user identifier
        creator - the creator name
        access - the type of access (public = true, private = false)
        Returns:
        true if the operation was successful

      • editMap

        boolean editMap​(int uid,
                int mid,
                java.lang.String name,
                boolean access)
        Edits a map selected by its id. If there is not map matching, it will modify nothing.
        Parameters:
        uid - the user identifier
        mid - the map identifier
        name - the new map name
        access - the type of access (public = true, private = false)
        Returns:
        true if the operation was successful

      • getSharedMap

        javax.ws.rs.core.Response getSharedMap​(int uid,
                                       int mid,
                                       java.lang.String sharedID)
        Returns a map selected by its id and his token. If there is not map matching or the access map is on private mode, it will return a null object.
        Parameters:
        uid - the user identifier
        mid - the map identifier
        sharedID - the sharedID token
        Returns:
        the map

      • deleteMap

        boolean deleteMap​(int uid,
                  int mid)
        Deletes the selected map. If there is not map matching, it will return a null object.
        Parameters:
        uid - the user identifier
        mid - the map identifier
        Returns:
        true if the operation was successful
